fields.description: The certificate payload of the application. This is computed by hashing the certificate information on the client. Example: `32c220482c68413fbf8290e3b1e49b0a85901cfcd62ab0738760568a2a6e8a50`
fields.name: CertificatePayload

fields.description: The company name of the application. This value is set by the creator of the application. Example: `Microsoft Corporation`
fields.name: CompanyName

fields.description: The Intune deviceId. Unique identifier for the managed device. Example: `92ce5047-9553-4731-817f-9b401a999a1b`
fields.name: DeviceId

fields.description: The name associated with the device in the intune database. Example: `JOHNDOE-LAPTOP`.
fields.name: DeviceName

fields.description: Indicates the type of elevation occured
fields.name: ElevationType

fields.description: The date and time when the application was elevated. Example:`2014-01-01T00:00:00Z`
fields.name: EventDateTime

fields.description: The file description of the application. This value is set by the creator of the application. Example: `Editor of multiple coding languages.`
fields.name: FileDescription

fields.description: The full file path of the application including the filename and file extension. Example: `C:\Program Files\vscode.exe`
fields.name: FilePath

fields.description: The version of the application. This value is set by the creator of the application. Example: `6.2211.1035.1000`
fields.name: FileVersion

fields.description: The sha256 hash of the application. Example: `32c220482c68413fbf8290e3b1e49b0a85901cfcd62ab0738760568a2a6e8a57`
fields.name: Hash

fields.description: The internal name of the application. This value is set by the creator of the application. Example: `VS code`
fields.name: InternalName

fields.description: The justification to elevate the application. This is an input by the user when the privilegeManagementElevationType is of type userConfirmedElevation or support approved elevation. This will be null in all other scenarios. The length is capped at 256 char, enforced on the client side. Example: `To install debug tool.`.
fields.name: Justification

fields.description: The name of parent process associated with the elevated process. This is always populated for both parent and child process types
fields.name: ParentProcessName

fields.description: Unique Identifier of the policy configured to run the application with elevated access
fields.name: PolicyId

fields.description: The name of the policy configured to run the application in elevated access
fields.name: PolicyName

fields.description: Indicates the type of elevated process
fields.name: ProcessType

fields.description: The product name of the application. This value is set by the creator of the application. Example: `Visual Studio`
fields.name: ProductName

fields.description: The result of the elevation action with 0 being success, and everything else being exit code if the elevation was unsuccessful. The value will always be 0 on all unmanaged elevation. Example: `0`. Valid values 0 to 2147483647
fields.name: Result

fields.description: Unique identifier of the rule configured to run the application with elevated access
fields.name: RuleId

fields.description: To identify if the elevation is initiated by system or user interaction
fields.name: SystemInitiatedElevation

fields.description: The User Principal Name of the user who performed the elevation. Example: `john@domain.com`
fields.name: Upn

fields.description: The type of user account on Windows that was used to performed the elevation.
fields.name: UserType
